<html>
<head>
  <meta charset='utf-8' />
  <title>Simple Statistics</title>
  <meta name='viewport' content='width=device-width,initial-scale=1'>
  <meta name='description' content='Simple Statistics: Statistical methods in readable JavaScript for browsers, servers, and people.' />
  <link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Source+Sans+Pro:400,700|Source+Code+Pro:400,500,700' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
  <link href='assets/bass.css' type='text/css' rel='stylesheet' />
  <link href='assets/style.css' type='text/css' rel='stylesheet' />
  <link href='assets/github.css' type='text/css' rel='stylesheet' />
</head>
<body class='documentation'>
  <div class='container'>
    <div class='clearfix md-mxn2'>
      <div class='fixed md-show fix-3 overflow-auto max-height-100'>
        <div class='px1 py1'>
          <a href='http://simplestatistics.org/' class='h2 px2 button block button-transparent'>Simple Statistics</a>
          <p class='px2 center'>
            v1.0.0
            <iframe src="https://ghbtns.com/github-btn.html?user=simple-statistics&amp;repo=simple-statistics&amp;type=star&amp;count=true&amp;size=small" frameborder="0" scrolling="0" width="100px" height="20px" style='vertical-align:middle'></iframe>
          </p>
          <p class='px2'>
            Statistical methods in readable JavaScript for browsers, servers, and people.
          </p>
          <div class='px2'>
            <input
              placeholder='Filter'
              id='filter-input'
              class='col12 block field-light'
              type='text' />
          </div>
          <div id='toc' class='px2'>
            {{#each docs}}
              <a
                href='#{{permalink}}'
                class='block bold'>
                {{name}}
              </a>
              {{#each members.static}}
                <a
                  href='#{{permalink}}'
                  class='regular block'>
                  .{{name}}
                </a>
              {{/each}}
              {{#each members.instance}}
                <a
                  href='#{{permalink}}'
                  class='regular block'>
                  #{{name}}
                </a>
              {{/each}}
              {{#each events}}
                <a
                  href='#{{permalink}}'
                  class='regular block'>
                  <code>â“” {{name}}</code>
                </a>
              {{/each}}
            {{/each}}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class='fix-margin-3'>
        <div class='px2 py2 mb2'>
          <p>Simple Statistics is a JavaScript library for statistical
          computing, including descriptive statistics, classifiers, distributions,
          regression, and clustering.</p>

          <p>The library can be used with node.js by installing it from
          npm:</p>
          <pre class='overflow-auto'>npm install --save simple-statistics</pre>

          <p>To use simple statistics in a client-side application,
          you can either bundle it with <a href='http://browserify.org/'>browserify</a>
          or <a href='https://webpack.github.io/'>webpack</a>, or
          <a href='http://simplestatistics.org/#download'>download a source code package</a>.
          </p>

          <p>Once you've installed simple-statistics, you can use it in node/browserify/webpack
          by requiring the package:</p>
          <pre class='overflow-auto'>var ss = require('simple-statistics');</pre>
          <p>Or if you've included a script tag on your webpage, the library
          will be available under the <code>ss</code> variable automatically.
          The methods documented below are available as methods off of this
          object, like <code>ss.sum()</code> or <code>ss.mean()</code>. For
          questions or bug reports,
          <a href='https://github.com/simple-statistics/simple-statistics/issues'>visit the issue tracker.</a></p>

        </div>
        <div class='px2'>
{{#each docs ~}}<div class='py1'>{{> section}}</div>{{/each}}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <script src='assets/anchor.js'></script>
  <script src='assets/site.js'></script>
</body>
</html>
